Here is a PHP function that accomplishes what you're asking. This function, `wordCount`, takes a string as an input, removes punctuation, converts the text to lowercase, and splits the string into an array of words. Then it uses an array function to count the unique words in the text.

```php
function wordCount($str) {
    // Remove punctuation
    $string = preg_replace('#[^\p{L}\p{N}\s]#u', '', $str);

    // Convert the string to lowercase
    $string = strtolower($string);

    // Split the string into an array of words
    $words = preg_split('/\s+/', $string, -1, PREG_SPLIT_NO_EMPTY);

    // Create an associative array whose keys are words and values are word counts
    $count = array_count_values($words);

    // Return the count
    return $count;
}

$str = 'Greetings, Planet Earth!';
print_r(wordCount($str));
```

